/*This code creates a portfolio website using HTML and CSS, with some JavaScript for interactivity. Here's a breakdown of its structure and components:

Head Section
Metadata: Includes character set, viewport settings for responsive design, and the page title.
Stylesheets: Links to external stylesheets for Font Awesome icons and local stylesheets (styles.css and responsive.css).
Body Section
Header
Navbar: Contains the logo, a hamburger menu for mobile navigation, and a navigation menu with links to different sections of the website (Home, Portfolio, About, Services, Contact Me).
Main Hero Banner
Introduction: Displays a greeting with the user's name, a brief description (Computer Science Engineering Student), and two buttons (Hire Me, Get Resume).
Portfolio Section
Featured Portfolio: Showcases various portfolio items such as Web Design, Web Development, SEO, Content Writing, WordPress Development, and Video Editing, each with an image, title, and description.
About Section
About Me: Provides a personal introduction, describing the user’s background, motivations, and experiences. Includes a photo of the user.
Services Section
My Services: Lists the services offered by the user, including Web Design, Web Development, SEO, Content Writing, WordPress Development, and Video Editing. Each service has an icon, title, and description.
Contact Me Section
Contact Form: Allows visitors to get in touch with the user by filling out a form with their name, email, phone, and message.
Contact Details: Displays the user's contact information including email, phone, fax, and address.
Footer
Copyright Notice: States that all rights are reserved and credits the user for creating the website.
Social Links: Contains links to social media profiles (Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, LinkedIn) with corresponding icons.
Scripts
Font Awesome: Script for loading Font Awesome icons.
Custom JavaScript: Links to a local JavaScript file (script.js) for any additional functionality.
The code is structured to be responsive, ensuring it looks good on different devices. The navigation menu adapts to mobile screens with a hamburger menu, and various sections are clearly defined to showcase the user’s skills, portfolio, and contact information effectively.


